--- In neat@yahoogroups.com, &quot;John Arrowwood&quot; &lt;jarrowwx@h...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Can one of the SVG experts offer me a brief tutorial of what the 
&gt; SVG would look like to just draw a bunch of lines and then do a 
&gt; bunch of labeled circles at the virtexes?

Sure...here&#39;s a simple SVG document:

&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;ISO-8859-1&quot;?&gt;
&lt;!DOCTYPE svg SYSTEM &quot;svg-19991203.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;svg xmlns:svg=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 750 700&quot; 
height=&quot;700&quot; width=&quot;750&quot;&gt;
&lt;circle stroke-width=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;black&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; r=&quot;10&quot; cy=&quot;50&quot; 
cx=&quot;50&quot;/&gt;
&lt;text style=&quot;font-size:3pt&quot; y=&quot;52&quot; x=&quot;42&quot;&gt;Circle 1&lt;/text&gt;
&lt;circle stroke-width=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;black&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; r=&quot;10&quot; cy=&quot;75&quot; 
cx=&quot;100&quot;/&gt;
&lt;text style=&quot;font-size:3pt&quot; y=&quot;77&quot; x=&quot;92&quot;&gt;Circle 2&lt;/text&gt;
&lt;path stroke-width=&quot;0.5&quot; stroke=&quot;black&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; d=&quot;M 60 50 L 90 
75&quot; id=&quot;4&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

The root tag is the &lt;svg&gt; tag, which defines the size of the canvas 
and the area to view.

The &lt;circle&gt; tag draws a circle, with the assigned attributes (which 
should be fairly self-explanatory).
The &lt;text&gt; tags put text in the specified position with the specified 
attributes, in this case inside the two circles.
The &lt;path&gt; tag draws a line, starting at &quot;M 60 50&quot; and terminating 
at &quot;L 90 75&quot;.

Presumably your document would contain hundreds or thousands of just 
these three types of tags.  

